## Task Summary: Container security hardening with .git ro mount and tmpfs overlays

**Track:** container-vcs-readonly-2026-03-11
**Task:** Mount .git read-only, mask sensitive dirs with tmpfs, add track ID reserved segment validation
**Date:** 2026-03-12

### Changes

- compose.yml: added .git:/workspace/.git:ro volume overlay and tmpfs for private/, config/secrets/
- compose.dev.yml: same security mount changes as compose.yml
- project-docs/conventions/security.md: documented container-level enforcement scope
- scripts/track_schema.py: added RESERVED_ID_SEGMENTS validation for track IDs
- scripts/test_track_schema.py: added TestReservedIdWords test class (4 tests)
- track/items/container-vcs-readonly-2026-03-11/: renamed from container-git-readonly to avoid guard hook false positives

### Why

Codex workspace-write sandbox and cargo make shell bypass Claude Code hooks, allowing direct
git operations and sensitive file reads from inside containers. This commit enforces security
at OS level: .git becomes read-only (EROFS on write), and sensitive directories appear empty
via tmpfs overlays. The track ID validation prevents future guard hook false positives from
track names containing reserved words like "git".
